title: [Documentation report] `Tensor.flatten()` does not show in latest documentations
body_html: Recently there is a method flatten() implemented, and already added to the docs file, it has been a month and still not shown in the latest documentation. Just quickly to make sure if it is an expected case (e.g. documentation has longer cycle to synchronize)

body: Recently there is a method `flatten()` implemented, and already added to the [docs file](https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/302adb7cc827adbcf5cd29c531cd8cbe52b2f7dc/torch/_torch_docs.py#L1613-L1635), it has been a month and still not shown in the [latest documentation](https://pytorch.org/docs/master/search.html?q=flatten&check_keywords=yes&area=default). Just quickly to make sure if it is an expected case (e.g. documentation has longer cycle to synchronize)
